snippet: Ireland qualified for the Rugby World Cup quarterfinals by squeezing past Italy, 16-9, at Olympic Stadium in London. The victory also lifted France into the final eight.
abstract: Ireland beats Italy, 16-9, moving on to quarterfinals of Rugby World Cup; other rugby news noted.
lead_paragraph: Ireland qualified for the Rugby World Cup quarterfinals by squeezing past Italy, 16-9, at Olympic Stadium in London. The victory also lifted France into the final eight.

headline.main: Ireland Advances at Rugby World Cup
